    <meta property="og:title" content="Lattice O–O ligands in Fe-incorporated hydroxides enhance water oxidation electrocatalysis - Nature Chemistry"/>
    <meta property="og:description" content="While the ligand coordination microenvironment surrounding catalytic centres influences reactivity, dynamic oxygen reconstruction during water oxidation electrocatalysis complicates structure-based mechanistic insights. Now the in situ formation of lattice O&#8211;O ligands has been shown to activate Fe centres in metal oxides and hydroxides, thereby enhancing their oxygen evolution reaction activity."/>
